{---------------------------------------------------------------------}
{ The AsciiCommands component can place into a project the ability to }
{ respond to 3 letter ASCII commands. It is an example of a serial    }
{ port application and contains a Comm package to manage the port.    }
{ The package is initialized by an Autostart Block on the Blocks side }
{ that calls Initialize. It is sufficient to copy|paste the           }
{ AsciiCommands package into another project. It will initialize      }
{ itself and respond to commands at 9600 baud, N, 8, 1. The           }
{ interpreter uses hash function indexed buckets for various command. }
{ patterns and is a general expression evaluator always returning     }
{ a command response. To continue the trail, open up the "Initialize" }
{ procedure. This will lead you to the MonitorCommPort routine.       }
{_____________________________________________________________________}

